The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 26 January is 184,175 (21,227.2 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 21 January, there were 9,096 new confirmed cases (1,048.4 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 14 January, there were 7,054 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 29% (2,042 extra cases).
